    fi
    whiptail --title "termio ŌĆö Encrypted Key Sync" --scrolltext --msgbox \
"Encrypted Key Sync ŌĆö Opt In

This feature stores your private SSH keys in an AES-256
encrypted archive (keys.enc) inside your sync folder.

What this means:
  - Your keys travel with your sync provider
  - Security depends on your passphrase strength AND
    your sync provider's security
  - The passphrase is NEVER stored anywhere by termio
  - You will be prompted each time keys are archived
